The paper deals with the problem of releasing private information from a database, which is a common topic in computer security (cs.CR) and data structures (cs.DS). The focus on releasing marginals and the use of differential privacy suggest that information theory (cs.IT) and machine learning (cs.LG) may also be relevant sub-categories. Finally, the use of databases and the need for efficient algorithms suggest that databases (cs.DB) may also be a relevant sub-category.
